references: Repealing: Ord 8700, Ord 10547, Ord 11101, Ord 11284, Ord 13152
summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 8700, entitled "An Ordinance concerning, designating and regulating persons engaged in the Police Department of the City of Seattle, and fixing their compensation", approved October 8, 1902, and Ordinance No. 10547, approved February 10, 1904, Ordinance No. 11101, became an ordinance pursuant to City Charter, July 23, 1904, Ordinance No. 11284, approved September 15, 1904, Ordinance No. 12081, approved February 14, 1905 and Ordinance No. 13152, approved January 3, 1906, amendatory thereof.
